President Obama and the First Lady will be traveling to Senegal, South Africa, and Tanzania from June 26 - July 3. The purpose of the trip is to reinforce the importance of the United States' ties with countries in sub-Saharan Africa. This includes expanding economic growth, investment, and trade, strengthening democratic institutions, and investing in the next generation of African leaders. The President will meet with leaders from government, business, and civil society, as well as youth, to discuss strategic partnerships on bilateral and global issues. The trip aims to deepen cooperation between the United States and sub-Saharan Africa to promote regional and global peace and prosperity.